To improve future versions of the Amiga MO FAQ, I would like to get hold of
the following:@{line}
@{lindent 4}@{pari -2}@{par}· Information on using MO disks with non-512-byte sector sizes with operating
systems like NetBSD, OpenBSD and Linux.@{line}@{par}
· Information about using IDE/ATAPI MO drives with the built-in controller of
the A600, A1200 and A4000. MO drives are also sold with PCMCIA adapters for use
with laptop PCs. I would like to know whether these can be used without special
software on the A600 & A1200.@{line}@{par}
· Reports of compatibility or otherwise of various Mac MO/SCSI driver software
products with different emulators.@{line}@{par}
· If you have drawn some nice Workbench icons for MO disks, I would like to
include them.@{line}@{par}
· Is the "MO-MIGA" software, formerly sold by Fourth Level Developments, still
available? This is mentioned in docs/misc/MO-MIGA.FAQ.lha on Aminet.@{line}@{par}
· Any other information which you think should be included.@{pard}@{par}

